<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-10-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-10-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="599" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d599">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-10-18"><hi rend="italic">October 18,
                                1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Minister ultramar admits that Cuban repertory is translation. English
                            version maintains that neither in ministry states nor elsewhere is there
                            any knowledge of a Spanish version signed by Spanish minister being in
                            existence. Minister ultramar promises to recognize Spanish version
                            attested by Spanish minister when received here. Have minister send such
                            copy at once. Meantime ultramar telegraphs to suspend proceedings
                            Aguilera case.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Taylor.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>